window.DOC_RIPASSO = "__Domande di Ripasso per lEsame di Human Behavioral Neuroscience \(Gemini\)__\n\n__Modulo 1: General Concepts & Neuroeconomics__\n\n__1\\. What is price?__\n\nQ1\\.1 According to the lecture material, which of the following best defines 'price' in a commercial transaction?\n\nA\\. The intrinsic utility of a product independent of market forces\\.\n\nB\\. The gravitational attraction of a commodity towards its natural value\\.\n\nC\\. The amount charged by the seller from the buyer in exchange for a product or service\\.\n\nD\\. The total cost of production plus the potential for future profit\\.\n\nQ1\\.2 The term 'price' can take various names depending on the context\\. Which of the following pairings is incorrect according to the slides?\n\nA\\. Rent : For the use of place or machinery\\.\n\nB\\. Salary : For the supply of professional services\\.\n\nC\\. Premium : In the case of insurance\\.\n\nD\\. Fare : In the case of transportation\\.\n\n__2\\. What is cost?__\n\nQ2\\.1 How is 'cost' defined in relation to the production of goods or services?\n\nA\\. The subjective value assigned to a product by the end consumer\\.\n\nB\\. The total amount spent on inputs \\(such as land, labour, and capital\\) to produce a product\\.\n\nC\\. The final amount paid by the consumer at the point of sale\\.\n\nD\\. The difference between the market price and the natural price\\.\n\nQ2\\.2 The slides identify three basic elements that constitute 'cost'\\. Which of the following is one of them?\n\nA\\. Market Demand\\.\n\nB\\. Consumer Surplus\\.\n\nC\\. Overheads\\.\n\nD\\. Inflation Rate\\.\n\n__3\\. What is value?__\n\nQ3\\.1 Which statement best describes the concept of 'value' as presented in the course?\n\nA\\. It is a fixed, objective measure equivalent to the production cost\\.\n\nB\\. It is the utility or benefit derived by the customer, representing what they perceive the product is worth\\.\n\nC\\. It is the exact monetary amount printed on the price tag\\.\n\nD\\. It is a constant variable that does not change between different people or places\\.\n... (backup truncated)